flawed_nl_solution:
If Tenisha has 40 dogs, the number of female dogs is 3/5*40 = 42
3/4 of the females give birth, meaning 3/4*42 = <<3/4*42=63/2>>63/2 female dogs gives birth to puppies.
Since each dog that gave birth had 10 puppies, the number of puppies that were born is 63/2*10 = <<63/2*10=315>>315
After donating 130 puppies to the church, Tenisha remained with 315-130 = 185 puppies.
